context1337-release
====================

This repository is an automated build-and-release pipeline. It does NOT contain
upstream source code; it clones pinned upstream commits at build time, applies a
small security patch, compiles, and publishes the resulting binaries + data as
GitHub Release artifacts.

Upstream sources (cloned at build time — see pins.json for exact commits)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

  * context1337  — https://github.com/wgpsec/context1337
      The `absec` MCP server (Go). Compiled here for multiple platforms.

  * AboutSecurity — https://github.com/wgpsec/AboutSecurity
      The pentest knowledge data set (skills / Dic / Payload / Vuln) that is
      indexed into builtin.db (FTS5) and bundled alongside the binary.

Both upstream repositories are authored by wgpsec. At the time this pipeline was
created, neither upstream repository carried an explicit LICENSE file. This
pipeline redistributes built artifacts derived from those sources for
interoperability/convenience; it claims no ownership of the upstream work.
Downstream users must confirm the upstream licensing terms with wgpsec before
relying on these artifacts. If wgpsec requests removal or adds license terms,
this pipeline and its releases should be updated accordingly.

Modification applied by this pipeline
-------------------------------------

  * Loopback-binding security patch (build.ts:patchLoopbackBinding):
    upstream `cmd/absec/main.go` hardcodes `http.ListenAndServe(":port")`, which
    binds 0.0.0.0 on every interface. The patch adds a `--host` flag defaulting
    to 127.0.0.1 so an auto-launched absec is not exposed on the LAN by default.
    No other source modification is made.

The build recipe (clone → patch → python FTS index → CGO_ENABLED=0 cross-compile
→ assemble + zip) mirrors the upstream build/Dockerfile.
